==Old English==
===Etymology===
From genitive of [[carl]] + {{Latinx|[[wægn|wǣn]]}}, literally the ‘peasant’s wagon’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'karlez wæ:n/}}

===Noun phrase===
{{Unicode|'''[[carles]] {{Latinx|[[wæn|wǣn]]}}'''}} ''m''
# An [[asterism]] of the seven brightest stars in the constellation of the [[Great Bear]], [[Ursa Major]]
#:''Carles wæn ne gæþ næfre adune under ðyssere eorþan, swa swa oðre tunglan doþ'': Carl’s Wain never goes under the earth as other constellations do. (''De Natura Rerum'')

